<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>15-702</num>
  <heading>Attorney fees taxed as costs.</heading>
  <text>An attorney for the District of Columbia may not retain attorney fees taxed as costs in litigation in which the District of Columbia is a party.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annoGroup>
      <heading>History</heading>
      <annotation>Dec. 23, 1963, 77 Stat. 531, Pub. L. 88-241, § 1</annotation>
      <annotation>June 19, 1986, 100 Stat. 633, Pub. L. 99-336, § 4(b)(2)</annotation>
    </annoGroup>
    <annoGroup>
      <heading>Prior Codifications</heading>
      <annotation>1981 Ed., § 15-702.</annotation>
      <annotation>1973 Ed., § 15-702.</annotation>
    </annoGroup>
  </annotations>
</section>
